obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (16074)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_33_52_00002_197733_1517807320974&sectionId=16074&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_33_52_00002_197733_1517807320974
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Salary and Allowances of`
  line `Leaders of Opposition in Parliament Act, 1977.`
  line
  line `(2) It shall come into force on such date^1`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. 1st November, 1977, vide notification No. G.S.R. 664(E), dated 1st November, 1977, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary,`
  line `Part II, sec. 3(i).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (16075)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definition.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_33_52_00002_197733_1517807320974&sectionId=16075&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_33_52_00002_197733_1517807320974
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, "Leader of the Opposition", in relation to either House of Parliament,`
  line `means that member of the Council of States or the House of the People, as the case may be, who is, for`
  line `the time being, the Leader in that House of the party in opposition to the Government having the greatest`
  line `numerical strength and recognised as such by the Chairman of the Council of States or the Speaker of the`
  line `House of the People, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--Where there are two or more parties in opposition to the Government, in the Council`
  line `of States or in the House of the People having the same numerical strength, the Chairman of the Council`
  line `of States or the Speaker of the House of the People, as the case may be, shall, having regard to the status`
  line `of the parties, recognise any one of the Leaders of such parties as the Leader of the Opposition for the`
  line `purposes of this section and such recognition shall be final and conclusive.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (16076)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Salary, and daily, constituency and sumptuary allowances.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_33_52_00002_197733_1517807320974&sectionId=16076&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_33_52_00002_197733_1517807320974
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[3. Salary, and daily, constituency and sumptuary allowances.--(1) Each Leader of the`
  line `Opposition shall, so long as he continues as such Leader, be entitled to receive a salary per mensem and`
  line `allowance for each day at the same rates as are specified in section 3 of the Salary, Allowances and`
  line `Pension of Members of Parliament Act, 1954 (30 of 1954) with respect to members of Parliament.`
  line
  line `(2) Each Leader of the Opposition shall also be entitled to receive a constituency allowance at the`
  line `same rate as is for the time being specified under section 8 of the said Act with respect to members of`
  line Parliament.
  line
  line `(3) There shall be paid to each Leader of the Opposition a sumptuary allowance of one thousand`
  line `rupees per mensem:]`
  line
  line ^2
  line `[Provided that on and from the 17th day of September, 2001, the sumptuary allowance shall be paid`
  line `to each Leader of the Opposition at the same rate at which the sumptuary allowance is payable, under`
  line `section 5 of the Salaries and Allowances of Ministers Act, 1952 (58 of 1952), to every other Minister who`
  line `is a member of the Cabinet.]`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 78 of 1985, s. 2, for section 3 (w.e.f. 26-12-1985).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 29 of 2002, s. 3 (w.e.f. 17-9-2001).`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (16077)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Residence for Leaders of Opposition.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_33_52_00002_197733_1517807320974&sectionId=16077&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_33_52_00002_197733_1517807320974
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) Each Leader of the Opposition shall, so long as he`
  line `continues as such Leader and for a period of one month immediately thereafter, be entitled without`
  line `payment of rent to the use of a furnished residence and no charge shall fall on the Leader of the`
  line `Opposition personally in respect of the maintenance of such residence.`
  line
  line `(2) In the event of the death of a Leader of the Opposition, his family shall be entitled to the use of`
  line `the furnished residence occupied by him--`
  line
  line `(a) for a period of one month immediately after his death, without payment of rent and no charge`
  line `shall fall on his family in respect of the maintenance of such residence; and`
  line
  line `(b) for a further period of one month, on payment of rent at such rates as may be prescribed by`
  line `rules made in this behalf by the Central Government and also charges in respect of electricity and`
  line `water consumed in that residence during such further period.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section, "residence" includes the staff quarters and other`
  line `buildings appurtenant thereto, and the garden thereof, and "maintenance" in relation to a residence`
  line `includes the payment of local rates and taxes and the provision of electricity and water.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (16078)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Travelling and daily allowances to Leaders of Opposition.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_33_52_00002_197733_1517807320974&sectionId=16078&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_33_52_00002_197733_1517807320974
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[(1)] Subject to any rules made in`
  line `this behalf by the Central Government, a Leader of the Opposition shall be entitled to--`
  line
  line `(a) travelling allowances for himself and the members of his family and for transport of his and`
  line `his family's effects`
  line
  line `(i) in respect of the journey to Delhi from his usual place of residence outside Delhi for`
  line `assuming office; and`
  line
  line `(ii) in respect of the journey from Delhi to his usual place of residence outside Delhi on`
  line `relinquishing office; and`
  line
  line `(b) travelling and daily allowances in respect of tours undertaken by him in the discharge of his`
  line `duties as Leader of the Opposition, whether by sea, land or air.`
  line
  line ^2
  line `[(2) On and from the commencement of the Salaries and Allowances of Officers of Parliament and`
  line `Leaders of Opposition in Parliament (Second Amendment) Act, 2002, a Leader of the Opposition and his`
  line `family, whether travelling together or separately, shall be entitled to travelling allowance at the same rates`
  line `and for the same number of return journeys as admissible to a Minister and his family under sub-section`
  line `(1A) of section 6 of the Salaries and Allowances of Ministers Act, 1952 (58 of 1952).]`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Section 5 renumbered as sub-section (1) thereof by Act 78 of 1985, s. 3 (w.e.f. 26-12-1985).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 56 of 2002, s. 3, for sub-section (2) (w.e.f. 17-9-2001).`
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (16079)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Medical treatment, etc., to Leaders of Opposition.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_33_52_00002_197733_1517807320974&sectionId=16079&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_33_52_00002_197733_1517807320974
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `Subject to any rules made in this behalf by`
  line `the Central Government, a Leader of the Opposition and the members of his family shall be entitled free`
  line `of charge to accommodation in hospitals maintained by the Government and also to medical treatment.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (16080)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Leaders of Opposition not to draw salary or allowances as Members of Parliament.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_33_52_00002_197733_1517807320974&sectionId=16080&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_33_52_00002_197733_1517807320974
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line No
  line `Leader of the Opposition in receipt of a salary or allowance under this Act shall be entitled to receive any`
  line `sum out of funds provided by Parliament by way of salary or allowance in respect of his membership of`
  line `either House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (16081)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Amenities to Leaders of Opposition.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_33_52_00002_197733_1517807320974&sectionId=16081&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_33_52_00002_197733_1517807320974
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to any rules made in this behalf by the Central`
  line `Government, each Leader of the Opposition shall be entitled to telephone and secretarial facilities.`
  line
  line `(2) Subject to any rules made in this behalf by the Central Government, each Leader of the`
  line `Opposition shall be entitled to a conveyance allowance of ^1`
  line `[three thousand rupees] per month:`
  line
  line ^2
  line `[Provided that where a Leader of the Opposition is provided with conveyance facility with a driver`
  line `for the purposes of security or otherwise for any period, he shall not be entitled to the conveyance`
  line `allowance for that period.]`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 7 of 1991, s. 2, for "three hundred rupees" (w.e.f. 1-10-1990).`
  line
  line `2. Proviso ins. by s. 2, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-10-1990).`
obj_root_law_sections_8_a:
  sectionId (16082)
  sectionNo 8A
  orderNo 9
  title `Advance to Leader of Opposition for purchase of motor car.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 3, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-10-1990).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_33_52_00002_197733_1517807320974&sectionId=16082&sectionno=8A&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_33_52_00002_197733_1517807320974
obj_root_law_sections_8_a_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[8A. Advance to Leader of Opposition for purchase of motor car.--There may be paid to a`
  line `Leader of the Opposition, by way of a repayable advance, such sum of money as may be prescribed by`
  line `rules made in this behalf by the Central Government for the purchase of a motor car in order that he may`
  line `be able to discharge conveniently and efficiently the duties of his office.]`
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (16083)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 10
  title `Notification respecting the date on which persons became or ceased to be Leaders of Opposition to be conclusive evidence thereof.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_33_52_00002_197733_1517807320974&sectionId=16083&sectionno=9&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_33_52_00002_197733_1517807320974
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `The date on which any person became or ceased to be a`
  line `Leader of the Opposition shall be published in the Official Gazette, and any such notification shall be`
  line `conclusive evidence of the fact that he became, or ceased to be, a Leader of the Opposition on that date`
  line `for all the purposes of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9_a:
  sectionId (16084)
  sectionNo 9A
  orderNo 11
  title `Exemption from liability to pay income-tax on certain perquisites received by a Leader of the Opposition.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 78 of 1985, s. 4 (w.e.f. 26-12-1985).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_33_52_00002_197733_1517807320974&sectionId=16084&sectionno=9A&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_33_52_00002_197733_1517807320974
obj_root_law_sections_9_a_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[9A.Exemption from liability to pay income-tax on certain perquisites received by a Leader of`
  line `the Opposition.--Notwithstanding anything contained in the Income-tax Act, 1961 (43 of 1961), the`
  line `value of rent free furnished residence (including maintenance thereof) provided to a Leader of the`
  line `Opposition under sub-section (1) of section 4 shall not be included in the computation of his income`
  line `chargeable under the heading "Salaries" under section 15 of the Income-tax Act, 1961.]`
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (16085)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 12
  title `Power to make rule.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 7 of 1991, s. 4 (w.e.f. 1-10-1990).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_33_52_00002_197733_1517807320974&sectionId=16085&sectionno=10&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_33_52_00002_197733_1517807320974
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `make rules for carrying out the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the rates at which rent shall be payable by the family of a deceased Leader of the Opposition`
  line `to the use of the furnished residence occupied by him under clause (b) of sub-section (2) of section 4;`
  line
  line `(b) the travelling and daily allowances admissible to a Leader of the Opposition under section 5;`
  line
  line `(c) the medical treatment admissible to a Leader of the Opposition and the members of his family`
  line `under section 6;`
  line
  line `(d) the telephone and secretarial facilities admissible to a Leader of the Opposition and the`
  line `conditions subject to which he shall be entitled to conveyance allowance under section 8;`
  line
  line ^1
  line `[(e) the advance payable to a Leader of the Opposition under section 8A.]`
  line
  line `(3) Every rule made under this section shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each`
  line `House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in`
  line `one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately`
  line `following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification`
  line `in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall thereafter have effect only`
  line `in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such modification or`
  line `annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that rule.`
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (16086)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 13
  title [Repealed.].
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
